GET /chat HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:3000
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade

Response:

HTTP/1.1 101 Switching Protocols
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade

After receiving:

101 Switching Protocols

The connection becomes a WebSocket connection.

Interview Question

Q: Why do we need an Upgrade request?

Answer: Browsers can only initiate connections through HTTP/HTTPS. The Upgrade header allows both sides to switch from HTTP to the WebSocket protocol.

5. Socket.IO

Many beginners think Socket.IO = WebSocket.

This is not true.

WebSocket
Protocol
Standard
Defined by RFC
Socket.IO
JavaScript library
Built on top of WebSocket
Provides extra features

Think:

WebSocket = Engine

Socket.IO = Car
Socket.IO Features
Auto Reconnection
io("http://localhost:3000");

If the internet disconnects:

Disconnected
↓
Reconnect automatically
Rooms
socket.join("room1");

Send message to specific room:

io.to("room1").emit("message");
Broadcasting
socket.broadcast.emit("message");

Send to everyone except sender.

Event-based API
socket.emit("message", "Hello");

socket.on("message", (data) => {
  console.log(data);
});

Much cleaner than raw WebSocket.

Fallback Transport

If WebSocket is unavailable:

WebSocket ❌
↓
Long Polling ✅

Socket.IO automatically falls back.

Socket.IO Connection Process
1. HTTP Request
        ↓
2. Polling Connection
        ↓
3. Upgrade Attempt
        ↓
4. WebSocket Connection

This is why in browser DevTools you often see:

polling
polling
upgrade
websocket
Complete Comparison
Feature	Polling	Long Polling	WebSocket	Socket.IO
Real-time	❌	Partial	✅	✅
Persistent Connection	❌	❌	✅	✅
Low Latency	❌	Better	✅	✅
Auto Reconnect	❌	❌	❌	✅
Rooms	❌	❌	❌	✅
Fallback Support	❌	❌	❌	✅
Protocol	HTTP	HTTP	WebSocket	Library
MERN Interview Answer (2-Minute Version)

If an interviewer asks:

Explain Polling, WebSocket, Socket.IO, and Upgrade.

You can answer:

Polling repeatedly sends HTTP requests to check for updates. Long polling keeps a request open until data is available. WebSocket solves this by creating a persistent full-duplex connection between client and server. A WebSocket connection begins as an HTTP request and then uses an Upgrade handshake to switch protocols. Socket.IO is a library built on top of WebSocket that provides features like automatic reconnection, rooms, broadcasting, event-based communication, and fallback to polling when WebSocket is unavailable.

English correction

Your question:

Websocket , socket io , polling , upgrade

A more natural way to ask:

Can you explain WebSocket, Socket.IO, polling, and the WebSocket upgrade process?

so to install websocket we have to do  npm i websocket ?

Not exactly.

WebSocket itself is a protocol, not something you must always install.

In the browser

WebSocket support is built into modern browsers:

const socket = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:3000");

No npm package is needed on the frontend.

On a Node.js server

Node.js doesn't provide a WebSocket server API by default, so developers commonly install the ws package:

npm install ws

Example:

const WebSocket = require("ws");

const wss = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 3000 });

wss.on("connection", (ws) => {
  ws.send("Connected!");
});
What about npm install websocket?

There is an npm package called websocket, but it is not the standard choice today.

Most Node.js projects use:

npm install ws

or

npm install socket.io

depending on requirements.

WebSocket vs Socket.IO installation
Raw WebSocket
npm install ws

Server:

const WebSocket = require("ws");

Client:

const socket = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:3000");
Socket.IO

Server:

npm install socket.io

Client:

npm install socket.io-client

Usage:

import { io } from "socket.io-client";

const socket = io("http://localhost:3000");
Interview Question

Q: Do browsers need a WebSocket package installed?

Answer: No. Browsers already provide the native WebSocket API. On the server side, libraries such as ws are commonly used to implement a WebSocket server.

English correction

Your sentence:

so to install websocket we have to do npm i websocket ?

More natural:

So, do we need to run npm install websocket to use WebSocket?

or

Do we need to install a package to use WebSocket?
Websocket , socket io , polling , upgrade 

These terms are all related to real-time communication between a client (browser/mobile app) and a server. They are commonly asked in MERN interviews.

1. Polling

Polling is the simplest technique.

How it works

The client repeatedly asks the server:

"Do you have any new data?"

Example:

setInterval(async () => {
  const response = await fetch("/messages");
  const data = await response.json();
  console.log(data);
}, 5000);

Here the browser sends a request every 5 seconds.

Flow
Client ---- Request ----> Server
Client <--- Response ---- Server

(wait 5 sec)

Client ---- Request ----> Server
Client <--- Response ---- Server
Problems
Too many unnecessary requests
Higher server load
Delay in receiving updates
Wastes bandwidth
Interview Question

Q: What is the drawback of polling?

Answer: Even when no new data exists, the client keeps sending requests, causing unnecessary network traffic and latency.

2. Long Polling

Improvement over polling.

Instead of responding immediately, the server keeps the request open until new data arrives.

Flow
Client ---- Request ----> Server

(Server waits)

New message arrives

Client <--- Response ---- Server

Client immediately sends another request
Benefits
Fewer requests than polling
Faster updates
Drawbacks
Still HTTP request based
Connection repeatedly opens and closes
Not truly real-time
3. WebSocket

WebSocket is a protocol that creates a persistent two-way connection between client and server.

After the connection is established:

Client can send data anytime
Server can send data anytime
No need for repeated HTTP requests
Flow
Client <===========> Server
        Open Connection
Example

Browser:

const socket = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:3000");

socket.onmessage = (event) => {
  console.log(event.data);
};

socket.send("Hello");
Benefits

✅ Real-time

✅ Low latency

✅ Full duplex communication

✅ Less bandwidth

Use Cases
Chat applications
Online games
Live stock prices
Notifications
Collaborative editors
Interview Question

Q: Why is WebSocket faster than polling?

Answer: Because a single persistent connection is maintained, eliminating repeated HTTP request-response cycles.

4. WebSocket Upgrade

A WebSocket connection starts as an HTTP request.

The client asks the server:

"Can we upgrade this HTTP connection to WebSocket?"

Handshake

Request:

GET /chat HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:3000
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade

Response:

HTTP/1.1 101 Switching Protocols
Upgrade: websocket
Connection: Upgrade

After receiving:

101 Switching Protocols

The connection becomes a WebSocket connection.

Interview Question

Q: Why do we need an Upgrade request?

Answer: Browsers can only initiate connections through HTTP/HTTPS. The Upgrade header allows both sides to switch from HTTP to the WebSocket protocol.

